text: The Tamang people are an Indigenous Native People of (baeyuls) Nepal. They speak there own tamangic Language.And once they have there own 12 zhong tamangsaling kingdom surrounded to Newa Nepa mandal after the saha dynasty all kingdom vanished . In Nepal, Tamang/Moormi people make for 1.539,830 persons, or 5.6% of the country's total population, up from 1.3 million in 2001. ==References==
